---
import AppShell from "../frontend/thinkinglabs-ui/components/AppShell.astro";
import ThinkinglabsUiPage from "../layouts/ThinkinglabsUiPage.astro";
---

<ThinkinglabsUiPage
  title="Privacy — thinkinglabs"
  description="thinkinglabs does not track visitors. No analytics, no cookies, no fingerprinting."
>
  <AppShell activeNav="Index">
    <section class="tl-page-head is-spacious">
      <div class="tl-eyebrow">/privacy</div>
      <h1>Privacy.</h1>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-privacy-lede">
      <p>This site does not track you.</p>
      <p>
        No analytics. No cookies set by the site. No fingerprinting. No pixels, no logs of who you
        are, no tooling that quietly aggregates a profile of your reading habits.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-privacy-grid">
      <article>
        <div class="tl-eyebrow">What is collected</div>
        <h3>Nothing about you.</h3>
        <p>
          The site is static HTML rebuilt from a markdown repository. There is no application
          server reading your requests, no third-party SDK loaded into the page, no
          client-side analytics call.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <div class="tl-eyebrow">What is stored</div>
        <h3>Nothing on your device.</h3>
        <p>
          No first-party or third-party cookies. No localStorage, no sessionStorage, no IndexedDB
          writes. If your browser has any storage entries from this origin, they are not put there
          by this site.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <div class="tl-eyebrow">Server logs</div>
        <h3>The host may keep request logs.</h3>
        <p>
          Edge or origin infrastructure can keep transient request logs (IP, path, user agent) for
          operational reasons such as abuse mitigation. Those logs are not read, joined, or shared
          by the site itself.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <div class="tl-eyebrow">Embedded media</div>
        <h3>External links open elsewhere.</h3>
        <p>
          Links to other domains follow your browser's normal behaviour and may be subject to those
          sites' policies. Nothing is embedded inline that loads scripts or images from a tracker.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <div class="tl-eyebrow">Contact</div>
        <h3>Reach out directly.</h3>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy or anything else go through the channels listed on
          <a href="/contact/">/contact</a>. The site has no form handlers.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </AppShell>
</ThinkinglabsUiPage>

<style>
  .tl-privacy-lede {
    width: var(--tl-center);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 6vh 0 9vh;
    color: rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.78);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 480;
    line-height: 1.32;
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
  }

  .tl-privacy-lede p + p {
    margin-top: 1.2em;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.62);
  }

  .tl-privacy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(2.4rem, 4vw, 3.4rem) clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    width: var(--tl-center);
    margin: 0 auto 18vh;
    padding-top: 4vh;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--tl-line);
  }

  .tl-privacy-grid h3 {
    margin-top: 8px;
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2vw, 22px);
    font-weight: 580;
    line-height: 1.22;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
  }

  .tl-privacy-grid p {
    margin-top: 10px;
    color: rgba(7, 9, 13, 0.64);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .tl-privacy-grid a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .tl-privacy-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
